OL,3,CStaff member at NHS trust that failed
OL,4,Cto stop triple killer speaks out
OL,6,FThe independent investigation found
OL,7,Fthat between 2019 and 2023 there were
OL,8,F15 other incidents at Nottinghamshire
OL,9,FHealthcare NHS foundation Trust, in
OL,10,Fwhich patients carried out "extremely
OL,11,Fserious" violence towards members of
OL,12,Fthe community.
OL,14,FIn three cases it resulted in deaths.
OL,15,FIn one incident a patient stabbed five
OL,16,Fpeople over the course of a weekend.
OL,18,FAnd yet, the report concludes, there
OL,19,Fwas an "absence" of action plans and
OL,20,Flearning.
